    • checkCheck

      public static boolean checkCheck(Piece[][] board, int landingRank, int landingFile, int movingRank, int movingFile, Piece landingPiece, Piece movingPiece, char turn)
      Checks whether or not the player is in check after performing the move
      Parameters:
      board - A 2D array of Pieces representing the chess board
      landingRank - An int representing the rank number of the destination of the piece that is moving
      landingFile - An int representing the file number of the destination of the piece that is moving
      movingRank - An int representing the rank number of the starting position of the piece that is moving
      movingFile - An int represnting the file number of the starting position of the piece that is moving
      landingPiece - A Piece representing the original piece at the destination
      movingPiece - A Piece representing the original piece at the starting position
      turn - A char representing which color's turn it is
      Returns:
      Returns true if the current player is not in check after performing the move
